undaries, or abstractions: an essentially free thinking that embodies creative novelty itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aPhilosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Ethics. 4aPhilosophy : History of Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Metaphysics. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Theology. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh1 aMcCullough, Lissa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWolfson, Elliot R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848508940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438485089423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438485089/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles